About Us

Study at our campuses in Tulsa, Los Angeles, Riverside and our recently acquired campus in Denver.

Spartan College is  excited to welcome Redstone College to the family. Redstone College was  established 1965 and offers programs in growing fields of Airframe and Powerplant  (A&P), Avionics and HVAC. Our faculty and staff in Denver are professional,  qualified instructors, and like the rest of our Spartan family, are committed  to helping you get into the right field and prepare for a successful career. The  Denver campus changed its name to Spartan College of Aeronautics &  Technology in March 2017.
For almost 90 years, Spartan College has helped  students break into the aviation and aeronautics field – and now, we’re extending  our reach. In addition to our campuses in Tulsa and Los Angeles and Riverside, now  we have a newly acquired campus in Denver.
At Spartan College, we strive to be one of the  best aviation and flight schools in the country by offering diploma, Associate  degree and Bachelor's degree programs to help you launch your career. We’re  also proud to provide training for the United States Air Force.

Hands-on learning at its finest

We believe students do best in a learn-by-doing  environment. Each program is designed to offer a broad set of general job skill  competencies, hands-on learning experiences and classroom lectures by our  experienced instructors.
At Spartan College, we realize many of our  students work part-time and full-time. To cater to the needs of our students,  we offer a full range of student services, such as student housing (offered at  both our Denver and Tulsa campus locations), scholarship opportunities, job  assistance, career services, libraries and activity centers, and financial aid  to those who qualify.
Take your passion for aeronautics to Spartan  College! Contact us today to learn how you can start your training.

































